# Blog Post Images

Images must **support the article**—show the actual feature, component, or page the post describes.

**Priority order:**

1. **Screenshot the actual work** — The feature, component, or page the post is about. E.g., for a before/after sliders post, screenshot the sliders; for a portfolio post, screenshot the home page.
2. **Unsplash** — If there's no obvious screenshot (generic topic, conceptual post), download a relevant image from Unsplash. Use `?w=1200&h=630&fit=crop`. Save to `public/blog/<slug>.png`.
3. **Omit** — If neither works, omit the `image` field; the gradient placeholder will be used.

**Screenshot script** (when the work is on the site):

```bash
node scripts/screenshot-blog.mjs <url> <slug>
```

For modals or scrollable content, use scroll options:

```bash
node scripts/screenshot-blog.mjs "http://localhost:3000/selected-work?case=get-shit-done" <slug> \
  --scroll-container "[data-case-study-scroll]" --scroll-y 1400 --wait 2500
```

**Unsplash fallback:**

```bash
curl -sL -o public/blog/<slug>.png "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-<id>?w=1200&h=630&fit=crop"
```
